name: the online discussion room
postTitle: Artificial Intelligence in healthcare - what do you think?

comments.content: Hello all, I personally think that AI definitely has a usage in health care, but more so as a supplementary tool. At least at the current stage.
AI has its benefits for any industry, but needs to be kept in check to prevent displacing job availability.
I think that there is a place for it, but it shouldn't be used as a crutch.  That the final word should always be a human doctor and their patient.
I think most situations require a physician or medical professional to determine if you need treatment and AI cant do a physical check up

It's definitely been proven to be useful in identifying cases that humans might overlook, but it's still learning. Once it builds upon its database and has a nigh 100% accuracy rate, then I would be interested in increasing its authority.
